			Inside this page at any section we can insert body of current page using @@body keyword.
		</li>
		<li>
			To specify the layout for any page we can use  @@layout [name of directive/page component].  
			In layout component page we have to use @@inherits LayoutComponentBase to use the @@Body
		</li>
		<li>

		</li>
</ul>


<h5>
		<a>
			Route templates:
		</a>
</h5>
		<ul>
			<li>
				The Router component enables routing to Razor components. The Router component is used in the App component (App.razor).
				If a razor file having @@page directive compile ,the generated component class is provided a RouteAttribute specifying the component's route template. that is used boy Routview
			</li>
			<li>
				When the app starts, the assembly specified as the Router's AppAssembly is scanned to gather route information for the app's components that have a RouteAttribute.
			</li>
			<li>
				At runtime, the RouteView component:

				<p>	a. Receives the RouteData from the Router along with any route parameters. </p>
				<p>	b. Renders the specified component with its layout, including any further nested layouts.</p>
				<p> c. Components support multiple route templates using multiple @@page directives. </p>
			</li>
		</ul>



